name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have heard from so many doctors, nurses, and others about having the real fear about not having the equipment they need. We received our share from the national stockpile, but like every other state, it wasn't enough.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have talked in the past about #PPE that doctors and nurses and other use. It should be no secret that we have a real shortage of #PPE. We're talking about masks, goggles, gloves, face shields - things to keep those on the front lines protected.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I want to thank our churches. They are doing amazing things online to bring services into homes while protecting people. Those of you still doing services, we ask you not to do that. It is not wise. It is a very real risk to your members and everyone else. Let's use technology.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The most important thing is that we cannot get through this by each hospital doing its own thing. The only way we get through this is by all hospitals in each region having one plan, one voice, and a commitment to work closely together as we move forward.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Today hospitals from 8 regions submitted their draft action plans for their capacity increase. @OHdeptofhealth and @OHNationalGuard are currently reviewing these and will get back with the hospitals soon.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I told you yesterday that we received a report from the @ClevelandClinic that the estimate that we will get hit hard by #COVID19 in the next few weeks and that we might not peak until mid-May. I also told you we may need to triple our hospital capacity.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: As the weather gets better and you want to be outside - that's great. But we ask you to continue #SocialDistancing. Take a walk, walk your dog - but it's so important to physically distance yourself from others.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I issued an order last night to our team that every state contractor with an essential state contract  - our team will go out and check that they are following best practices. They've always been subject to this, but now we're going out to make sure.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have nurses, doctors, and others who need these masks. WE would be able to sterilize 160,000 per day. This is a matter of life and death. We need to protect or people who are risking their lives. @US_FDA - Please approve this.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@Battelle has developed new technology to sterilize surgical masks. They've had a real breakthrough. As soon as it is approved by @US_FDA we can begin using these. This is very exciting. I mention this because I appeal to the FDA - Please give us the approval to use these.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Staffing at hospitals is a major issue. We're trying to pull people in who have been retired; maybe other doctors, like dermatologists, can play a different role in helping during this crisis. #InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There is a real sense of urgency to what I'm doing and what my team is doing every day. It is going to take doubling or tripling our hospital capacity. We have a lot of work to do and we need you to stay far apart.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All you have to do is look at the news coming out of NY, Lousiana.... this virus is not respecting state lines and it multiplies just as well no matter what state it is in. It is coming.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The evidence indicates that cases will double every six days. This is a train that is moving. It starts slowly, but it will start moving faster and faster and faster.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you don't believe that we could see 10,000 new cases a day -- We've tried to describe what the science tells us. Hospitals looking at the modeling and say that this is coming. It's here.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We haven't issued an order about travel, but people who come into #Ohio, we would ask them to self-quarantine for 14 days.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are going to do what we need to do to protect Ohioans. We've asked health departments and police: If you see something that you think is a hotspot of people gathering together - very nicely tell them they can't congregate.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: More than ever folks, stay home. Everything we are doing is goes far to #FlattentheCurve. We have bought time in #Ohio to allow these hospitals system to gear up. We have to keep buying that time. Don't lighten up.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Our hospital capacity is about a third of the blue curve. We're really ramping up our build-up of hospitals now.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Here is the curve from @OhioState: Yellow is unmitigated. But, at the peak of the mitigated (blue) curve we are now projecting 10,000 new cases in #Ohio a day. pic.twitter.com/EHPIZVAYCt

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: Any one of us could end up needing hospital services. We're starting to see that while most of us are riding it out at home, we don't know how everyone's body is going to react. pic.twitter.com/RYIHzeSbBC

tweet: We've divided the state into 8 regions and I've asked each region to have their collective draft plans on my desk by 9am tomorrow. I've asked them to have a final draft by noon on Monday. I've asked @OHNationalGuard to oversee this buildup.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: In addition, they say at the projected peak, we need to go up 3x in our hospital capacity. We have a long way to go. This is the stark reality. The good news: the hospitals have all been planning for this. But now we are closing up the planning and moving toward the action. pic.twitter.com/Mj8GaYHF04

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@ClevelandClinic told us that within about 2 weeks it will kick in much harder, according to their modeling. They project we may not hit the peak until mid-May.

tweet:

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: What we do now will determine if we overrun #Ohio's hospitals and get to a situation where our medical teams are making life and death decisions. We don't want to be in that position. I worry about this every day. Stay home.  #InThisTogetherOhio #StayHomeOhio #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: Based on the best data we have currently in #Ohio, at the #COVID19 peak surge - we could be seeing 6,000 to 8,000 new cases a day. The more we can push that surge off, the better hospitals can prepare their systems.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Re: schools - Is is possible we don't get back to school this academic year? Absolutely. But we just don't know yet. Our teachers, administrators, parents - they're doing amazing work with distance learning.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Again, distance is the key. Keep the distance. It's tempting as the weather gets nice to go to playgrounds - we want you to go outside - but you have to keep your distance.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Playing basketball: It's a great sport, but in our call today with a number of mayors, at least 2 of them said they've taken the basketball hoops down.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: They are willing to do this to help Ohioans live, thrive and stay healthy -- they are just asking us to stay home, practice social distancing, don't create the spread that puts these workers at risk. We will get through this faster if we all act responsibly.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: One doctor asked me to relay this message: It's very scary for the people working in our hospital systems. These nurses and doctors are putting their lives and their families' lives at risk by doing their jobs.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The people who stock the grocery store, the people who deliver the food - they are all people with families. I think of the technology companies, the utilities -- we are grateful for their service. And of course, first responders, nurses, doctors.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .LtGovHusted: If you can work from home, that is how you should operate even if you are an essential business. But there are some people who can't do that - and they are the real heroes.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: Voting: Go to  http://vote.ohio.gov  to request your absentee ballot and find more information on the election process. If you can't print or acquire an absentee ballot - please call your local board of elections and they will mail you one.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Do not call your local health department or police department to ask how to interpret the order. Only call them if there are concerns about violations. Do not call 911 for this.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: A daily issue I've been trying to address about the #StayHomeOhio order and #EssentialBusiness list. It is important that you read the order. Use your good judgment in following the order. pic.twitter.com/9z53zWu4yw

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: We are going to hit peak capacity in our hospitals, and the folk with #COVID19 will be staying longer, which is why we need to increase the capacity in our hospitals. Everything you are doing matters. #InThisTogehterOhio pic.twitter.com/IlBPJuvoyA

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Healthcare Resources: We know that we are going to almost double what we're using when the surge comes. We will go above the current capacity. We are doing unique things to build the capacity that we need. -@DrAmyActon pic.twitter.com/kF3XwgFaa9

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: What you are doing at home is helping us maximize our #PPE. By doing what we're doing, we're making our supplies go longer. We would have needed 65x our typical usage, but with what we're doing we've lowered this to needing 40x more. pic.twitter.com/lCboNWBGN5

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Weddings/Funerals: These are not prohibited, but we ask that we don't have large gatherings. Postpone the big ceremony -- get married, but the big party should be after this is over. It's something to look forward to.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Evictions: We want everyone to stay home, and we want everyone to have a home to stay in. The bill passed by the legislature relieves the courts' requirement to hear criminal, civil, and administrative cases in a certain period of time.

tweet: .@DrAmyActon:  Wearing a mask does work - it won't stop a virus from coming in, but it can help prevent droplets from getting out if you sneeze or cough. I'm glad that folks are working on creating masks and sterilizing masks. There are all sorts of innovations happening.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I was just assured that the  http://unemployment.ohio.gov  website is up and running and there have been no failures to this site today.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted - The package moving through Congress would have some relief for 1099 small business owners. We don't know all the details, but we will be prepared to implement them as soon as we can.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are talking with the best people we can find, the experts. I've been talking with other governors about how we coordinate the expansion of hospitals -- because we want, no matter where you live, you to have access to the healthcare you need.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All our decisions have been based on the best information we could get. The essential job of the government is to protect people, especially the most vulnerable. These decisions weren't easy but they were based on protecting Ohioans' lives. #InThisTogetherOhio pic.twitter.com/r3mr2OGkAQ

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We hope everyone is back in business shortly, but we don't think this will peak until May 1. The only way we slow it down is with physical/social distancing.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are starting to take action today against a company, and we expect it won't be the last company -- businesses that clearly are not essential but remain open.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you look at the challenges facing the state, so many of them - mental health, drug addiction - are connected to public health. That is why I picked @DrAmyActon to lead @OHdeptofhealth -  to build up public health.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I've said many times that we must focus more on public health in #Ohio. Historically in this country we've underfunded public health. One of the lessons from this pandemic will be that we have to consistently fund public health in the United States.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The team reassures me that they are doing all they can, working overtime, to keep this site up. We are truly sorry for anyone who is having problems with the website. I ask for your patience as we work to solve this problem.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: @LtGovHusted: Re:  https://unemployment.ohio.gov/  - There has been a massive influx of people visiting the site. There were over 400,000 contacts through the website yesterday from people seeking information.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Even if you aren't an essential business, these safe work environment standards are going to last for a while as we come out of the situation we're in. Everyone should prepare themselves to follow these standards.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Please do not call law enforcement, the health department, or the #COVID19 helpline to ask for advice on if you are an essential business. Business owners must read the order and make their own judgments.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: You do not need a letter, certification, or clearance, but it is recommended that you create a document about why you believe you are an essential business and how you are providing a safe workplace.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: On the #StayHomeOhio order, we ask you to just read the order. It's on the website at  http://coronavirus.ohio.gov . You need to use your own good judgment of that order to make your own determination if you are essential.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have also learned that the Development Services Agency has secured approval from the US Dept. of Health & Human Services to extend the Winter Crisis Program from March 31 to May 1.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: We’ve just received a U.S. Department of Transportation has cut red tape related to obtaining or renewing CDLs and other licenses that are vital to the efficient movement of essential goods across the state and country. pic.twitter.com/6oMzepvHzp

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I'm really proud of all the young people at home. I want all of you at home to keep spreading the word and staying at home! #StayHomeOhio #InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Right now a bill that will help ease regulations and provide assistance for our fellow citizens is making its way through the General Assembly.   I look forward to signing it. We are #InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The Ohio Senate and House are in session and I am so grateful to them for quickly passing legislation to help us help our fellow citizens.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are grateful to the delegation for working on expanding unemployment assistance, helping individuals, aid to hospitals, food aid, small business loans, and transportation assistance are just some of the many ways the federal government is helping the states through this crisis

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We will get through this. We know we need to get back to work, but we have to get through this first.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
➡️Save lives. 
➡️Get the economy moving. 

We're doing what we are doing so that we can do both.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All of us have the same goal: save lives, and do what we can do now so that we can get out of this as quick as we can to get people back to work.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We need to #FlattenTheCurve because an overwhelmed hospital system will have long-term ramifications in regard to our ability to recover.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Each proactive step we take to protect people against #COVID19 is a step we take to prevent our economy from crashing. We are at war with a real enemy, and we must beat the enemy.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Don't forget to find all this information on  http://Coronavirus.ohio.gov/businesshelp

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Commercial lending: The banks, credit unions tell me that if you are a business owner experiencing difficulties, call them. They will work with you, they want to help you through this difficult period.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: The financial services industry wants me to remind you that they are open. Their lobby may not be open, but they have ATMs and drive-thrus, online services.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you are in a position to work at an essential business that is hiring, please do so.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I never recall a day where everyone can be part of the solution. We want you to be part of the solution, not part of the problem.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The goal is for all of us to work collectively to slow the spread. If you can stay home, do that. The virus only spreads when we allow it to happen through our behaviors.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you are open, you must remember to keep a safe environment for your employees. You don't want to have a violation that causes an employee to become sick and then it spreads through your workforce.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Businesses: You do not need a letter or certification to show that you are in compliance, but you do need a rationale about how the order applies to you.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Don't call law enforcement or the local health department and ask them to interpret it for you.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: What you are doing to #FlattenTheCurve is taking the pressure off the healthcare system. In the worst-case scenario, if we had done nothing, the estimate is there would be 6,000 new cases a day. What you are doing is making all the difference.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are going to get our economy back, but we have to get through it, protect as many lives as we can, and then move forward. I'm looking forward to that day, but it's not yet here.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: When people are dying and people don't feel safe, the economy is not going to come back. We have to #FlattenTheCurve so that when the wave comes, it's not as big as it would have been and we are prepared for it.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If our hospitals are overwhelmed thousands of Ohioans will not get the care they need. If our nurses and doctors get sick, if they die because we do not have facilities to protect them, that is a personal tragedy for them and for all of us.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The truth is that protecting people and protecting the economy are not mutually exclusive. In fact, one depends on the other. We save our economy by first saving lives. And we have to do it in that order.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I've been asked if I had a reaction to the President's statements yesterday. I think we are aligned. We want to get this over with ASAP. We want people back at work. The frustration he has, I share it. Each day we can't move forward is frustrating. We're all in this together.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Let me talk about our economy. Every single day I think about those of you who are unemployed. I think about the small businesses. I know that each day that goes by that you don't have income is very, very tough. And I fully understand that.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This is why have asked dentists and veterinarians to conserve their supplies. This is why we are asking private businesses who use this equipment – like the construction industry – to conserve their supply in order to share it with our first responders. pic.twitter.com/450UCmXQOv

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Just for some perspective, over a 24-hour period, on average, 36 pairs of gloves are used to care for 1 patient in intensive care. This is why we have ordered non-essential or elective surgeries to be postponed.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: PPE stands for Personal Protective Equipment – and it means the masks, gloves, gowns, face shields and goggles that are needed for our first responders. Our commitment is to do all we can to get first responders what they need.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are in the process of modeling with several partners. @InnovateOhio is bringing people in from the private sector to help us with this so that we can deal with what is coming. We know what is coming b/c we've seen it happening in other countries and states. We're getting ready

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are doing this through #SocialDistancing. We are also doing this by working on the capacity of beds in healthcare systems and the capacity of equipment, #PPE.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: As we have watched different countries and other states, it is important for us to remind you of our goal to #FlattenTheCurve. We have to do what we are doing so our healthcare system is not overwhelmed. Not only for #COVID19 patients but also for other emergencies.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I do not anticipate that @OHNationalGuard will have a role in the enforcement of the #StayHomeOhio order. That would be in the scope of local law enforcement and the health departments.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Re @OHNationalGuard: This mission will get broader in the sense that they will be doing more things in regard to the #COVID19 crisis. We are responding to what the medical community is asking for.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This is b/c we don't want someone to come in from jail, and they have a virus, and they are introduced into the general population.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: When new people come into the prisons from county jails, the director of @DRCOhio has created a system for these people to stay at reception and they are there for five weeks.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Re: Prisons -- There is a risk in prisons, but testing will be done any time there is testing that should be done.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We fully expect that companies that are open, that they must follow safety measures. Employees must feel safe. There has to be distance. Employees shouldn't be there if they are sick. If they violate that, the companies would be violating the law.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We hope the law doesn't have to actually be applied, we hope people will follow the order. We wouldn't have issued this if it wasn't a matter of life and death. This is a matter of life and death. We felt it was in the best interest of the people and necessary to save lives.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I would suspect that if there is a violation, that authorities would go and talk with the people involved and give that person a warning. Then they'd have to make up their mind how to react - if violations will be issued - based on how individuals act after that warning.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: These orders can be enforced by the local health dept. and local law enforcement, but we're not looking to see arrests and citations issued.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We don't want to be in a situation in #Ohio where we are in the middle of the surge and haven't had the chance to prepare.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: There will be a hospital surge. It is just a matter of how big it is. My goal for Ohio is that we don't waste a single day to be ahead of the curve.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We don't want to keep these orders on one second more than we have to. I'm very much aware of how much suffering is going on right now, people who have lost their jobs. I do not take that lightly. It weighs on me, but we have to protect life.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: If your business is part of the essential supply chain, you can stay open. BUT: You must ensure a clean, safe workplace. If you can't do that, you should not be open.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Manufacturers: Most companies have been able to do #SocialDistancing. Most have been able to adjust do that. Our request is for manufacturers to keep social distancing. They should also keep a healthy environment, make sure employees are not sick.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: If you can be an essential worker, if you can show up, you are absolutely needed. It is nothing less than noble and patriotic.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We ask that everyone - local governments too - to prepare for the long run to supply services people need. The earlier we prepare the better we will be. #TeamOhio is going to get through this, and we're going to win. #InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All of these brought unique challenges. but what happened with all of these incidents is that state revenues go down, but demand for health and human services go up. So we are tightening the belt early on.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
Unfortunately, this will be my third experience with an economic crisis since serving in state government:
•9/11
•The financial crisis of 2008
•and now the coronavirus pandemic.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you are an essential business you have to operate in a safe manner, a healthy work environment. You are an important part in the supply chain that we all need. We appreciate all that everyone is doing to make this happen.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: We get a lot of advice on what we should do, and we appreciate it. It is always that balance of acting quickly and being mindful of people and businesses. pic.twitter.com/ZJ3jDpFtEF

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The truth is: The most important thing we can all do right now is stay at home unless you are absolutely essential to those lifelines of food, water, transportation, our frontline workers. This is the real world we are living in.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: We are in a situation in the short term where we must do everything in our power to keep people home. We have to slow the spread. The #StayHomeOhio order is crucial. We have got to stay home while we stop spread and build hospital capacity. pic.twitter.com/olssKAyCQr

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: All the #PPE we have is going out today. We are talking small boxes, not truckloads, of #PPE. This is what we have. We are getting everything we have out to those who need it. We are waiting on federal shipments because we need more.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Everything we can do without having face to face is important b/c some of the greatest spread is happening in our nursing homes and hospitals.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I encourage healthcare providers to take advantage of telehealth. If anyone is at home sick, ask about everyone in their household. If anyone is sick, the entire household should be in isolation.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Our hospitals have been hard at work. We're doing some testing in house, some through private labs -- private labs are lagging. We need hospitals to report their data immediately to @OHdeptofhealth and @Cdcgov.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: I want to talk with our nursing home colleagues. I'm hearing amazing stories from the front lines. Staff are working tirelessly to take care of residents. The folks in our nursing homes are doing a heroic job. #InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I want to reemphasize that we worked with businesses in #Ohio --- they expressed that we need consistency in the supply chain. They want states to be consistent, and this is what is consistent with what industry groups leading this conversation say is needed. @LtGovHusted

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
Everyone should read the #StayHome order so that you understand what you can do and what you shouldn't do. 

(Our website is a little overwhelmed right now, but you will see it via multiple sources soon.)

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We don't look to see a bunch of people arrested. This is not what we want to accomplish. By doing the #StayHome health order, we can convey the seriousness of this. The businesses that stay open must figure out how to follow these guidelines.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have the ability to do religious services other ways. I implore religious leaders to think about their congregations. Gathering in groups is dangerous.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We did not order religious organizations to close, but my message to EVERYONE is that this is serious. When you are coming together, whether in a church or wherever - this is dangerous.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There are miracles around the corner that could change the trajectory, but right now what we have is the Governor, this #StayHome order, and what each one of us is doing to slow the spread. These are the weapons we have now and we must use them. We will be so sorry if we don't.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: There is no doubt in my mind that we have to ratchet down what we are doing in society. Listen to Italy begging us not to make mistakes -- you're hearing it from folks who are ahead of us in this curve. We don't have a day to spare.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There is hoarding going on of these medications. This rule limits it to a 14 day supply. This drug is essential to many with diseases and there is a shortage. We have to use it judiciously. It is important that we are thoughtful about our drug supply. -@DrAmyActon

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: In the future, we'll talk a lot about #PPE. We are maximizing what we have, and we're working with the federal government to get more, but we have a number of businesses in #Ohio that are working to make #PPE for us.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The lesson of history time after time has been if you don't do these things early enough you pay the price -- and the price you pay is a lot of people dying. #StayHomeOhio #InThisTogetherOhio #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Again -- this is an order, but it's a reasonable order that is consistent with what has to be done. If everyone cooperates we'll save a lot of lives. The healthcare system won't get overwhelmed. Use common sense. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: But, it should not be business as usual. This is not a joke. It is not a drill. We must limit exposure. This will help save lives. This is the time that you will see quiet descend on our country - as it should - so we can protect those who protect us. - @DrAmyActon

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Going outside: You can go out in your yard, visit the @OhioStateParks -- just keep your #SocialDistancing. Get out and walk --- this is important for mental health. Walk your dog, go hiking.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Eating out: Carryout is still ok. We advise people to do #SocialDistancing, but they can still pick up food.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There is word of a new test that is rapid, but it could be a month before it is online. So, for now, most will not be tested and just advised to stay home and take care of themselves. I know this sounds scary, but this is the truth.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: There is still an incredible shortage of testing supplies in #Ohio. We have to save the testing for frontline first responders and those at the highest risk.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Businesses should take a look at the #StayHome health order. It is an order, not a suggestion, and we expect people to comply. #InThisTogetherOhio #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There are businesses all over the state hiring by the thousands. Amazon, Walmart, Kroger, Meijer, Giant Eagle, Discount Drug Mart --- this info is there for you at  http://ohiomeansjobs.com

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This portal includes information on unemployment benefits, the Small Business Administration’s (SBA) Economic Injury Disaster Loan Program, the Liquor Buyback Program, modified rules for trucking to help ship critical supplies into the state, the delay of BWC Premiums, etc.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: •Today, we are announcing that businesses and workers can now access all of these resources in one place at:  http://Coronavirus.ohio.gov/BusinessHelp

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I see a vision of a future that is brighter than we have known. I know it in my heart and soul. Please, don't feel like this is pulling us apart, I believe this is binding us to each other, but it must be all of us who makes these sacrifices.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
@DrAmyActon: 

Do not be afraid. I am not afraid. I am determined. 

Everyone is being heroic right now. Every action to takes matters. 

This is our one shot. 

I already envision a future that is full of hope. Hope is essential.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: There is no time left. Listen to what Italy is telling us. Today is the day. We must do everything we can in our power to protect the people on the frontlines - the first responders and healthcare workers.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
Keep children of parents who work at the same employer together. 

Limit parent interaction at drop off and pick up.
 
The program will operate until April 30, with the potential to extend and adjust as needed.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
The order also says that: 

Ratios of one teacher to no more than six children. 

Limit use of shared space - If shared space is used, it must have a rigorous cleaning schedule.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All childcare centers, beginning on Thursday, must operate under a Temporary Pandemic Child Care license. We will also go down to a maximum of six children per room. This is a dramatic change, but it's necessary to minimize the risk to these kids. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The obvious concern about daycare is that when you put a large number of kids together, social distancing doesn't work well. Little kids share everything. It is time to move to the next stage - our goals are to keep kids, families, and workers safe.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Daycare: The number of kids in daycare has gone down dramatically. At the beginning of this, there were 117,000 kids in daycare subsidized by #Ohio. That number has gone down to 17,000. We don't have good numbers on private daycares.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The orders can be enforced by the local health departments and local law enforcement. It will go into effect at 11:59 tomorrow and stay in effect until April 6. We'll reassess then.  #StayHomeOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
Each business that stays open must follow good protocol in regard to health. Again, nothing new - nothing we haven't already been talking about: #SocialDistancing, washing hands, separate operating hours for at-risk populations, etc. 

#InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The second part of the #StayHomeOhio order talks about essential workers and businesses. We used the Homeland Security guidelines. These are the accepted businesses that are essential for us to continue to live.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: You can leave home to take care of others. You can take care of your neighbor, your family, your friend.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: #StayHomeOhio: It does permit exceptions to staying home. Common sense exceptions: leaving for health and safety, for necessary supplies and services, for outdoor activity (walking your dog, going to a park -- although playgrounds are closed).

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There is nothing in the order that we haven't already been talking about. There is nothing in this that I haven't been asking you to do for the last few weeks.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We will put this order online shortly.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are now at a new stage. .@DrAmyActon just signed a statewide #StayHome order for Ohioans.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are in a crucial time in this war. What we do now will slow this invader so that our healthcare system will have time to treat those who have come down with #COVID19 and also have time to treat everyone who has had another medical problem. Time is of the essence.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
We are Ohioans.

We are Buckeyes.

We are Strong.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
We haven't faced an enemy like we are facing today in 102 years. We are at war. In the time of war, we have to make sacrifices, and I thank all of you for all you are doing, all you are refraining from doing. You are making a huge difference. 

#InThisTogetherOhio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Put these cases back to back and think about that. Which side of this do you want to be on? Tough times show our character: either selfish or selfless.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: But another story: a person essential to keeping the unemployment system running had a relative on their deathbed, but that state employee chose not to visit their loved one because they had to keep the system running for the people who need it. It was a selfless act.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: A grocery store told me about a fight breaking out over toilet paper. Come on, folks. We have to be better than that. We have to treat each other better than that.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Let me make it clear: I will air on the side of protecting people. The bad behavior, the reckless behavior, must stop. The protection of life is the most important obligation that I have.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Sadly, however, I'm hearing of businesses that are recklessly risking the lives of their employees, their families, and everyone those employees come in contact with. This must stop. Please. Do what is right.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I want to thank the businesses who have gone out of their way to keep employees and customers safe. We have heroes out there in the business community. What you are doing every day is saving lives. There is no doubt about that.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I'm fully aware that some of our orders have caused people to lose jobs. Each order was agonized over. We made these decisions to save lives.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Throughout this crisis, I have tried to balance the safety of the people of #Ohio, but also try to achieve the continuation of essential services to keep our economy moving.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Our grave concern is about the danger of seniors being together and the spread of #COVID19.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I'm assured that each center has taken care to ensure that those who depend on food, will get it. It will be delivered to their homes. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Senior Centers: I am signing an executive order today that will go into effect at the close of business on Monday. All facilities providing older adult day care services and senior centers will close.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I want to thank all our first responders and everyone in the medical community. They've been working so hard to prepare. They are our heroes, and we are so grateful. #COVID19OhioReady #InThisTogether

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The beginning of the Psalm is also well known.   “The Lord is my Shepherd, I shall not want.”  For a while it is going to seem like we are living in the “valley of the shadow.”   But we will get through this.   The sun will come out and shine upon our state.  Our beautiful #Ohio.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
The 23rd Psalm tells us that: 
“Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil; for thou art with me; thy rod and thy staff comfort me.”

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: When confronted with the finality of death in the Judeo-Christian traditions,  we often turn to Scripture for Comfort.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: When we hear about these deaths, most of the time we won't know the individual. It will be another number, but we must remember that when we hear about a death, it was someone who was loved, someone who wanted to live longer.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have now entered a new phase of our battle with #COVID19. Yesterday, #Ohio had its first death from the #coronavirus. It was someone who @LtGovHusted and I knew very well. He was very well respected by everyone who knew him. All of us extend our deepest sympathy.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We all have it within ourselves to stop #COVID19 from spreading from one human being to another. It can't spread if we don't help it.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Re: shelter in place -  We've already asked people to shelter in place if they can. We've asked people to stay home if they can. Some of this is just terminology.  If there is no good reason to be out - stay home. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: This is real. This is accelerating. It's heartbreaking. Every bit of this is heartbreaking. These are some of the hardest things we'll face. Please heed our guidance. #COVID19

tweet:
.@LtGovHusted: 

Employers: Visit  http://workforce.ohio.gov . We have a list of a variety of ways you can up-skill during this time. When we come out of this, the digital economy is going to be strong. This is the time to up-skill your workers.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: An update on the #PrimaryElection: @FrankLaRose is not seeking a new election, just to extend the voting period to June 2. That means, if you already voted, you won't need to do it again. #Ohio

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Many have already started voluntary programs on deferrals for cars, credit cards, mortgages. Call them if you are in need. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: I was on a call with several financial CEOs - they asked me to emphasize to you to stay calm. The banking system is well. Your banks will be there for you and you can count on them.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: To the public: please respect those who are working. We are all going through a difficult time, give workers personal space. Help make sure you're protecting them and protecting yourself. We're all #InThisTogether.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: All the businesses that are open are open b/c they need to be - and we ask every business that is open to care about their employees. They are a vital link to the supply chain. Do everything you can to make your workplace healthy.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: Grocery stores want to emphasize that the supply chain is intact. Because of the excess demand, that's why you don't see it on the shelves. They can only go so fast, so if we crowd the stores, we create a problem for everyone else.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: Ohio did apply with @SBAgov for #SmallBiz and non-profits to be able to apply for low-interest loans. That request has been approved. The loans can be used to pay for fixed debts, payroll, accounts payable, and other bills.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: I sat in on a call with the President, they did commit that they are working with the private sector for a new supply of masks, tests, and ventilators. #COVID19

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: One thing you can do now is donate blood. If you are healthy go to  http://redcrossblood.org  or your local blood center. Your blood will be needed.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: For all of us: We cannot feel bad if we need help right now. There is help. None of us should feel shame if we need help.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: Young people: Take this seriously. Young people are turning out to be equally affected in Europe. You have to take this seriously. You have to help us not spread this virus. Viruses do not discriminate. They love us all equally. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady pic.twitter.com/jr6FVNPAlQ

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Take this seriously so that we can protect our essential workers. Every day matters - this will become increasingly clear. #COVID19OhioReady #COVID19 #InThisTogether

tweet: .@OhioDeptofAging: If you must visit -- use basic common sense - wash your hands, check ahead on how they are feeling before you make the decision to enter someone's home. #COVDI19 #COVID19OhioReady

tweet:
.@OhioDeptofAging: Here is what we need from you: 

Call your older loved ones, check on them. Ask them how they're feeling. Offer to go to the store or run errands. Pick up their medication.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioDeptOfAging:  I would say to those using these sites, I would encourage you to think of alternatives. We are working to ensure that senior citizens still have services they depend on.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioDeptOfAging: #Ohio has the 6th largest older adult population in the nation. Senior centers and adult day centers are important for meals, but they are sites were people congregate.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioMedicaid: Telehealth also allows us to protect families and practitioners from obtaining or spreading the #COVID19. This is important not only to Medicaid recipients but to everyone. Many private insurance companies are starting to expand telehealth, too.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioMedicaid: Enabling services to be done remotely is a good way to take the pressure off of emergency rooms and hospitals while allowing Ohioans to continue to receive quality care and not have to leave the home.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioMedicaid: We're expanding Medicaid access to these services so that patients won't have to go to the office or the hospital - they can talk to experts over the phone or online.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@OhioMedicaid:  Governor is issuing an executive order that will expand access to medical and behavioral health services using telehealth.

tweet:

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Temperature Checks at Businesses: Thermometers are in short supply, but I am just asking employers to be extremely careful with their employees. If you can't check employees' temps, ask them to take their own temperature at home.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
Returning from Spring Break: If you have been traveling, please stay in your home when you return. Make sure you aren't in contact with those outside of your household. 

Anyone thinking about traveling: Please reconsider. 

#COVID19

tweet: .@LtGovHusted: This week we had 78,000 requests for unemployment. Two weeks ago we had about 6,500. But know this - there are many businesses that are a critical part of the supply chain that need you. These businesses are overtaxed - those options are out there for work.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Everyone is in this fight. We don't need to go into the battlefield -- we simply need to stay home. Have space, no matter where we are. We need to stay socially connected but physically separated. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady #FlattenTheCurve

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This enemy is dangerous and it is using us as its host to survive and multiply --- but we do have it among our ability to fight back. When we stop moving, it stops moving! Each one of us must do all we can to limit our exposure. #COVID19OhioReady #FlattenTheCurve

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: #COVID19's mission is to reproduce. But it can't do its damage without us. We have it within our own control how fast it spreads and how widespread it spreads. We have our own safety and that of our fellow citizens in our own hands.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Efficiently using our testing to better understand the spread of the virus. This has to be done in a targeted way. Here is the truth: With our without a test the virus is here. It lives among us. And we must be at war with it. We're at war with a very dangerous, lethal enemy.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We must reserve the testing for those who are the sickest and the most at risk. #COVID19

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If you are feeling symptoms of #COVID19 , the most responsible, heroic, patriotic thing you can do is stay home. Your family should stay home. If your symptoms worsen - especially if you have difficultly breathing - you should go to the ER.

tweet: #COVID19 Testing: Testing is limited. It will, in all likelihood, remain limited. But please, do not fixate on testing. The vast majority of Ohioans who have symptoms do not need to be tested for the virus. If you are feeling symptoms, you should act like you have it.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: No one alive has seen anything like this, so it's understandable that it's taking awhile for people to wrap their heads around this. It's my job to be as honest as I can with people and tell our citizens what we know when we know it. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: If you understand that we're all in this together, we will all get through this. Donate blood, drop off food to a food bank, drop off food to an elderly neighbor -- these are things we can all do to help us collectively get through this together. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I'm pleading with parents: If you have children in daycare and can keep them home, please do it. To close daycares overnight won't work, but it's coming. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I've tried to signal that daycares will eventually be closed. But, our healthcare systems need to be staffed. You'll start to see healthcare facilities creating their own daycares. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The governor can only do so much. The choices you make will impact not just you, but your family, and those who you don't even know. You have to make these individual decisions. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We will get through this, I don't know how long it will take, but we want as many Ohioans to make it through as possible. People will die if we don't make these decisions. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: If we don't take these actions now, it'll be too late. This is a matter of life and death. We have to do this to save lives.  #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: What we've done this week is drastic action, but we're taking these steps to save lives. W/ no intervention we could expect 40%-70% of our population would contract this virus. We've made dramatic interventions to make a difference & stop our healthcare system from imploding.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Schools: Three weeks likely won't be enough time to be closed. It is likely we will have to extend this order. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Because #COVID19 affects our older adults, we will be issuing guidance shortly to close Ohio’s senior centers and adult daycare facilities. We aren't ordering that today, but it will be coming up. We will work to ensure all elderly adults continue to receive meals.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We know what we are all going through together will have a tremendous economic impact on businesses. This is our first step to help mitigate that. I want to thank all the businesses that have been working with us to come up with these ideas mentioned today.  - @LtGovHusted

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted -- We are working with the federal government to allow #SmallBiz and non-profits to apply for low-interest loans to pay for certain expenses incurred by #COVID19. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: ODJFS will also waive employer penalties for late reporting and payments for the next quarter to assist employers impacted by lack of staff availability.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Because we do not want to penalize individual employers for the impact of this outbreak by increasing future taxes, the costs of these additional benefits will be mutualized.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Ohio currently has a 1 wk waiting period before an individual can receive unemployment.  In order to expedite the payments to impacted Ohioans, we are waiving the waiting week so that workers eligible for unemployment benefits will receive them for the first week of unemployment.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This also applies to companies that determine it is necessary to temporarily shut down operations due to the current emergency. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We are broadening current state policy to clarify that individuals that are quarantined by a health professional or by their employer are considered to be unemployed and will not be subject to requirements to actively seek work during the period of emergency.  #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: To assist #Ohio workers directly impacted by the #COVID19 health emergency, I will issue an executive order that makes several changes to Ohio’s unemployment law and state agency policy. #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@LtGovHusted: We know how difficult this will be on business owners and employees. Please continue to use carryout and delivery as options -- we don't want to overwhelm grocery stores. Please continue to use your local restaurants. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: This is the real thing. This is not a drill. This is a once in a lifetime pandemic, and everything we all do matters.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: .@DrAmyActon: We need nurses and doctors, firefighters and EMS, not to be sick right now. It is a civic duty to keep those folks safe too. We know a firefighter has been confirmed as #COVID19 positive - now that entire firehouse has been exposed.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: @DrAmyActon: Everything we are doing is trying to slow the spread that we know is coming. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: It takes a few weeks from the first onset of infection (when you don't know you have it) to when you are in the ICU. Deaths are going to happen in the weeks after that. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

tweet: I also want to emphasize that anyone over the age of 60 is at significantly increased risk. If you normally rely on elderly grandparents to provide childcare, please consider alternatives. This is the time where we look to neighbors and friends to provide support.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: The recommendation is that you remove your child from daycare if you can. Children, unless they have a preexisting condition, they are probably going to get through it ok, but they are potential carriers.  #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Daycares: We are not closing them at this point, but it could happen in the future. Parents using daycares should start thinking about what their alternatives could be. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet:
.@LtGovHusted: We sent a letter to @realDonaldTrump and @Mike_Pence asking for additional waivers. We also are requesting access to more personal protective equipment for healthcare workers. 

#COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Our job is to do everything we can to help people get through this and offer a system for support. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: #Ohio will work with school leaders to make sure they have the flexibility to offer as many learning opportunities to students as possible. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I want to salute #Ohio's teachers. We are grateful for what you do every single day. As we go through a crisis like we've never lived through before, you are at the forefront of this as you continue to educate our kids during this period of time. #ThankYou for taking this on.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Due to our mild winter, many calamity day lesson plans prepared by teachers are still sitting on classroom shelves. There’s never been a better time to deploy these lessons.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Children can still read books. Anyone who has not signed their young child up for @ImaginationOhio, I encourage you to do so.  This program provides free books for kids ages birth to 5. They’re mailed to your home. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: But learning is possible event without internet. Kids can still explore the great outdoors to learn about nature. Stay six feet away from others, but kids and adults can go outside.  #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Many schools have plans for online learning options, and there are a wealth of free, online resources, like @KahnAcademy that schools and educators can share with students. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: There are many ways schools can extend students’ education, even when they are not in a classroom. Each school is different, but our request to every school is that you do all you can to keep education going. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Yesterday, I announced that after the final bell Monday, all of #Ohio’s K-12 schools will close for 3 weeks to curb the spread of #COVID19. I want to be clear: ALL physical K-12 buildings will close to kids, but learning should continue. pic.twitter.com/3jbegTTfVI

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: Schools will be able to provide every child under 18 with “grab and go” meals, ensuring that no child goes hungry while school is out. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: I am pleased to announce that in the past 24 hours, @USDA approved two of #Ohio’s waiver requests to keep school breakfast and lunch programs going while schools are closed. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady pic.twitter.com/aBn3T8SiEB

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We have announced in the last few days some very tough measures for #Ohio. My commitment to you is that we will do all we can to support and help people as we get through the next few weeks and months.

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: We'll be issuing an order for our community jails and community corrections facilities throughout the state prohibiting visitation. We also ask that other protocols be put into place to screen vendors, contractors, etc. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

tweet: The purpose of these orders is to help #Ohio keep social distancing. Our citizens must not only take steps to protect themselves but to also protect others. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

tweet: This order does NOT apply to religious gatherings or gatherings for the purpose of exercising First Amendment protected speech. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

tweet: It does NOT apply to typical office environments, schools, restaurants, factories, or retail or grocery stores where large groups of people are present but it is unusual for them to be within an arm’s length of one another. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: FOR CLARITY: a mass gathering does NOT include normal operations at airports, bus and train stations, medical facilities, shopping malls, shopping centers or other spaces where 100 or more people may be in transit. #COVID19 #COVID19OhioReady

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: This includes auditoriums, stadiums, arenas, large conference rooms, meeting halls, cafeterias, or any other confined indoor or outdoor space. This also includes parades, fairs, and festivals. #COVID19OhioReady #COVID19

name: Governor Mike DeWine

name: Governor Mike DeWine
tweet: What we are seeing with #COVID19 is predictable, and we have the ability to control risk. Everything in life involves risks, but we should not take unnecessary risks.

name: Governor Mike DeWine

tweet: Shortly, we will be issuing rules in regard to mass gatherings in #Ohio. Every expert has told us that there is a risk in any kind of mass gathering - the closer you are to other people, the bigger the risk. You must ask yourself if going to a large gathering is necessary.
